# Docs & phase hygiene

## Phase status

- Tick `docs/DEVELOPMENT_PHASES.md` checklist items (`- [ ]` → `- [x]`) in the same task that completes them.
- When a phase finishes (or partially), update the phase heading status and the Master Implementation Progress list together.
- Do not implement a later phase’s feature unless the user explicitly asks.

## Changelog

- Every completed implementation task needs a **newest-first** entry at the top of `docs/CHANGELOG.md` (under the intro), matching existing shape:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — <scope> · <short title>

- <what changed>
```

## ADRs

- Do not silently contradict `docs/ADR-000*.md`. Surface conflicts and ask for direction.

## Before “done”

- Run the `task-close` skill / checklist (phase, API spec, DATABASE.md, CHANGELOG, ADR if needed, lint/tests).
